text.section:
A carrier shall disclose to a Maryland resident applying for coverage under an out-of-state association contract:
that coverage is conditioned on membership in the association that holds the out-of-state association contract;
all costs related to joining and maintaining membership in the association;
that membership fees or dues are in addition to the premium for coverage under the out-of-state association contract;
that the terms and conditions of coverage under the out-of-state association contract are determined by the association and the carrier;
the mandated benefits required under Subtitle 8 of this title that are not included in the out-of-state association contract;
that the Maryland resident may purchase an individual health benefit plan that includes the mandated benefits under Subtitle 8 of this title that are not included in the out-of-state association contract from a carrier licensed and authorized to do business in the State;
that benefits offered under the out-of-state association contract are not regulated by the Commissioner; and
that the terms and conditions of coverage under the out-of-state association contract may be changed by agreement of the association and the carrier without the consent of a member.
